To rotate the matrix, you can use a transpose and reverse approach, where you first transpose the matrix (i.e., swap its rows with columns) and then reverse each row.

```python
def rotate_matrix(m):
    n = len(m)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i, n):
            m[j][i], m[i][j] = m[i][j], m[j][i]
    for row in m:
        row.reverse()
```
